  "textPreview": "Free June 9 event: How to win brand visibility when AI decides what gets seen →\nSolutions\nTools\nResources\nPricing\nEN\nSign in\nRequest a demo\nStart free trial\nBacklink Checker\n\nYou have 5 free backlink checks remaining today\n\n*.domain.com/*\nDomain with subdomains\nAnalyze\n\nTrusted by 40,000+ agencies\n\nAll your link building insights in one powerful Backlink Checker\n\nPerform an in-depth analysis of any backlink profile with this free backlink checker tool. Get fast, accurate results and a comprehensive database.\n\n1\nReferring domains\n\nDomains linking to the analyzed domain/URL\n\nDomain and Page Trust scores\nBacklinks\nBacklink toxicity score\nNew and lost referring domains\nBroken backlinks\nLooker Studio report\n1\n2\n3\n4\n5\n6\n7\nStart free trial\nExpand your business with our reliable, up-to-date backlink data\n\nOur enhanced Backlink Checker database opens access to top-quality backlink insights\n\n2.7T\nBacklinks indexed\n420M\nDomains indexed\n6B\nPages crawled daily\nFreshness\n\nSE Ranking delivers some of the freshest backlink data out there, with 58% of backlinks updated every 90 days. It also identifies new links in a flash.\n\nRelevance\n\nSE Ranking’s rapid updates cut down on irrelevant backlinks, enhancing the quality of your analysis. This also lets the Backlink Analysis tool display the Domain Trust metric with pinpoint precision.\n\nCompleteness\n\nSE Ranking’s database is among the largest on the market, with 2.9 trillion backlinks and 411 million referring domains indexed. Our constantly expanding database results in comprehensive reports and easy backlink lookups.\n\nGranularity\n\nSE Ranking’s Backlink Checker delivers actionable insights. Get key metrics like toxicity score, dofollow/nofollow ratio, Domain and Page Trust scores, and more. Evaluating backlink quality has never been easier and more efficient.\n\nCheck backlinks right away\n\nThis powerful SEO Backlink Checker unlocks any website’s backlinks to help you find backlink opportunities\n\n*.domain.com/*\nDomain with subdomains\nAnal",
